OL,6,FThose who died in the incident were
OL,7,FErin McQuade, 18, a student at the
OL,8,FUniversity of Glasgow, and her
OL,9,Fgrandparents Jack Sweeney, 68, and
OL,10,FLorraine Sweeney, 69, from Dumbarton,
OL,11,FWest Dunbartonshire; primary school
OL,12,Fteacher Stephenie Tait, 29, and tax
OL,13,Fworker Jacqueline Morton, 51, both
OL,14,Ffrom Glasgow; and Gillian Ewing, 52,
OL,15,Ffrom Edinburgh. Fifteen people were
OL,16,Finjured.
OL,18,FThe city's Royal Exchange Square was
OL,19,Fpiled high with floral tributes
OL,20,Ffollowing the crash, and a candle-lit
OL,21,Fvigil was held in George Square.
